  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health emergency response to Burundian refugees in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With CERF funds, WHO will procure and deliver essential medicines and supplies to health centers inside Mahama refugee camp and to the Bukora health center and Kirehe District Hospital that are receiving referral cases.  In particular, WHO will replenish vaccines and other emergency medicines loaned by the Rwandan Ministry of Health for immunization activities for newly arrived refugees from Burundi.  Supplies and medicines will be delivered and utilized within four months.  In addition, WHO will support disease surveillance activities for early detection and response to potential disease outbreaks in the camp.</narrative>
  </description>
